SSH will refuse to use a private key that is too broadly accessible, so restrict its permissions.

Move the .pem file to a stable folder, e.g., C:\Users\YourUser\.ssh\soc-ec2-key.pem

Open Windows Terminal (PowerShell)

Run (adjust path and username):

icacls "C:\Users\YourUser\.ssh\soc-ec2-key.pem" /inheritance:r

icacls "C:\Users\YourUser\.ssh\soc-ec2-key.pem" /grant:r "$($env:USERNAME):(R)"

This makes the key readable only by your user
